rComments: I would consider him as a very nice prof, even though his lecture could be very dense and heavy sometimes. However, if you work hard on understand the readings then there wouldnt be a problem. His grading criteria is very clear. I would definitely take one of his courses again if theres a chance.

This prof doesnt post over half of the readings. If its not in the textbook and its not one of the few he posts then good luck because youre never finding them. Ive tried. Most arent found online and half of the books are never available. Plus idk what tf hes saying in lecture.

So hard to understand what the heck he is saying. Its not that be has an accent, but he slurs his words together making it impossible to catch everything he says. Also his lectures are pretty useless, all the lecture content is taken directly from the textbook. If you read the textbook you don't need to show up. Super easy, very basic knowlegde.
